/*1> Write a Java program to determine whether a given integer number is a Sunny number. A number is called a sunny number if the number next to the given number is a perfect square. In other words, a number N will be a sunny number if N+1 is a perfect square.
Example :  N=80 then N+1 will be 80+1=81, which is a perfect square of the number 9. Hence 80 is a sunny number.*/
import java.util.*;
class Sunny 
{
	public static void main(String[] args) 
	{
		Scanner s=new Scanner(System.in);
		System.out.println("Enter a number:");
		int n=s.nextInt();
		int sr=(int)Math.sqrt(n+1);
		if(sr*sr==n+1){
			System.out.println("Sunny number");
		}
		else{
			System.out.println("Not a Sunny number");
		}


	}
}
